public class Solution {
  public int binarySearch(int[] array, int target) {
    if (array == null || array.length == 0) {
      return -1;
    }
    int left = 0;
    int right = array.length - 1;
    while (left <= right) {
      int mid = left + (right - left) / 2;
      if (array[mid] == target) {
        return mid;
      }else if (array[mid] > target) {
        right = mid - 1;
      } else {
        left = mid + 1;
      }
    }
    return -1;
  }
}

没什么难度，唯一就是注意不要rule out the target, so you need to be very careful about the "<=" at while loop 
 '
 while (left <= right) {
 '


